☢ Soon, my music will be properly recorded, mixed, and unleashed, upon everyone. As someone diagnosed with heavy ADHD, Im used to operating FASTER than everyone around me. As someone unofficially diagnosed with OCD, I cant help but see patterns. As someone who is diagnosed with BiPolar disorder, I tend to lose myself in these musical experiments. I was born a passionate slave to logic and math, its a drug to me and its how my mind works. I get high on this focus. These riffs are based off of 3s and 4s, which multiply into 6ths, 9ths, 12ths, and 16ths. 3, and 4, are universal, cosmic values. Want to understand? 🏁 🌴 Available bubble caps! They are all $45 plus $5 for shipping, get em while theyre still around! These caps arent sloppily blown into a rough sphere and then tapered and given a rough, flame-popped opening for the nozzle. These caps are meticulously shaped until the walls are at least 4-5mm thick and the center is a perfect sphere. The nozzle is then carefully blown onto the piece and the air channel inside is made to be either 2mm, 3mm, and sometimes 4mm for special occasions before being saw-cut and polished in the flame for a clean nozzle. There is no tolerence for this step, the final product is exact, whereas the size of the sphere of the cap requires less precision. 1mm in the nozzle of a cap at that size drastically changes the airflow! Lastly, the handle is blown on and shaped to provide a nice counterweight, as well as a comfortable grip to help prevent dropping! Fortunately, this design has been drop-tested and has even survived more than one drop onto asphalt, so you can be sure every cap is built to be durable, and function like a champion. Pictured here are four caps, two of which have "Short-Nozzles", one of which has a medium, and the blue cap with the dichhroic metal in it is a "Long-Nozzle". Thank you profoundly for viewing and supporting my work. 🌴🏁
